## Cloud Auth / IAM Failure
**Symptom:** `AccessDenied`, `Unauthorized`, or expired credentials.  

### Likely Causes
- IAM policy missing action (`ec2:DescribeInstances`, `s3:GetObject`, etc.)
- Expired/rotated key, stale token
- Wrong ServiceAccount binding (K8s/GCP/Azure)  

### Fix
```hcl
# Terraform IAM Policy Snippet
resource "aws_iam_policy" "read_only" {
  name   = "read_only_access"
  policy = jsonencode({
    Version = "2012-10-17"
    Statement = [{
      Effect   = "Allow"
      Action   = ["s3:GetObject"]
      Resource = "*"
    }]
  })
}
